## Audit scope (LOCKED facts honored)

Treat the spawn-load OOM as **pool exhaustion during live instantiation of ~18,478 objects**, with victim stacks that name **last allocators**, not necessarily leak sites. Owner attribution is broken (fact #6). `SwgCuiAllTargets` is a known but **minor** leak; `garbageCollect` there did **not** stop OOM (fact #8).

---

## Subsystem alloc/free audit

### Verdict on the dominant path

In the named skeletal / object / template subsystems, I did **not** find a per-object **missing `delete`/`release`** on the normal **create → live → destroy** path that would explain ~1.3M live blocks at OOM. The stacks in fact #4 are consistent with **mass legitimate instantiation** (~70 small blocks/object × 18,478 objects ≈ census in fact #5), not a single runaway leak in `Skeleton.cpp` or `GroundScene.cpp`.

What follows are **balanced paths** and **actual imbalances** (minor or conditional).

---

### `clientSkeletalAnimation`

| Site | Allocation | Matching free | Load-path note |
|------|------------|---------------|----------------|
| `Skeleton.cpp:791,797` | `new Segment(...)` in ctor | `~Skeleton` `PointerDeleter` on `m_skeletonSegments` (`827-828`) | One skeleton graph per appearance LOD; freed when appearance dies |
| `Skeleton.cpp:1886,1893` | `new uint8[...]` transform backing stores | `allocateTransformArrays` deletes prior stores (`1868-1879`); `~Skeleton` deletes arrays (`819-823`) | Realloc-safe; not a leak |
| `BasicSkeletonTemplate.cpp:518` | `return new Skeleton(...)` | Owned by `SkeletalAppearance2::m_skeletons`; `~SkeletalAppearance2` `PointerDeleter` + `delete m_skeletons` (`1262-1263`) | Balanced |
| `SkeletalAppearanceTemplate.cpp:297-327` | `SkeletonTemplateList::fetch`, `fetchBasicSkeletonTemplate`, `createSkeleton` | `basicSkeletonTemplate->release()` (`340`); `std::for_each(..., release)` on skeleton templates (`349`) | Per-appearance build is ref-count balanced |
| `SkeletalAppearanceTemplate.cpp:426` | `return new SkeletalAppearance2(this)` | `Object::setAppearance` / `~Object` delete appearance (`883-886`, `1551`) | Balanced |
| `SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1013-1125,1080,1083` | `AnimationEnvironment`, skeleton/mesh vectors, resolver, shader-prim vectors | Full teardown in `~SkeletalAppearance2` (`1183-1278`) | Balanced |
| `SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:2252-2271` | `compositeMesh.addShaderPrimitives` → new SBSSPs | Old LOD vector swapped out then `PointerDeleter` (`2267-2271`) | Rebuild replaces, does not accumulate |
| `MeshConstructionHelper.cpp` (static scratch via `SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3429-3561`) | Temp mesh build data | `clearAllData()` deletes per-shader/per-TRD scratch (`499-505`) after each `addShaderPrimitives` (`3560-3561`) | Shared singleton helper; cleared per mesh build |
| `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:482` | **Not an alloc site** — `prepareToView()` | N/A | OOM stack line is render-time, not load leak |
| `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:394-1151` | `_initialize`: streams, index buffer, `m_sourceData`, render commands | `~SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` (`430-447`) | Large **per-instance** cost when mesh builds; expected retention while object lives |

**Minor / tooling imbalances (not 18k-scale):**

```615:616:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearanceTemplate.cpp
	// @todo remove the fetched MeshGeneratorTemplate from m_meshGenerators.
```

```651:652:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearanceTemplate.cpp
	// @todo remove the fetched SkeletonTemplate from m_skeletonTemplates.
```

Editor `removeMeshGenerator` / `removeSkeletonTemplate` can leave fetched template refs in `m_meshGenerators` / `m_skeletonTemplates`. Not the cantina spawn path.

**Asymmetric but intentional template caching:**

```490:501:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SkeletalAppearanceTemplate.cpp
		for (MeshGeneratorTemplateVector::iterator it = m_meshGenerators.begin(); it != endIt; ++it)
		{
			if (*it)
				(*it)->garbageCollect();   // does NOT release fetch ref
		}
```

vs skeleton/LAT refs released in the same function (`506-525`). Preload pins MGT data in the SAT template until SAT dtor (`125-131`). That is **cache retention**, not a per-spawn-object leak; it does contribute to **working set** during `WorldSnapshot::preloadSomeAssets` (1173 templates preloaded).

